<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-5811] InvokerInvocationException not being unwrapped</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-5811</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When methods compiled static are mixed with methods not compiled static and calling the closure, InvokerInvocationException is not unwrapped. Code depending on original Exception won&apos;t work.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;See attached Groovy class.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If compiled with 2.0.5, following output should be printed&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;First: WRONG&lt;br/&gt;
Second: WRONG&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If all static compilations are disabled, everything is ok&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;First: OK&lt;br/&gt;
Second: OK&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Ubuntu 10.04 x64</environment>
