                            <comment id="14473474" author="melix" created="Mon, 26 Nov 2012 10:11:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Smaller code showing up the issue:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; groovy.transform.*

@InheritConstructors
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;MyException &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;extends&lt;/span&gt; Exception {}

void foo() {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throw&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; MyException()
}

@CompileStatic
void bar() {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;boolean&lt;/span&gt; caught = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {
        def cl = { foo() }
        cl()
    } &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; (MyException e) {
        caught = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;
    } &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;finally&lt;/span&gt; {  
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;assert&lt;/span&gt; caught
    }
}

bar()
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14473536" author="melix" created="Tue, 27 Nov 2012 08:57:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The issue will only be fixed in &lt;tt&gt;2.1.0&lt;/tt&gt; because it involves a change in &lt;tt&gt;Closure#call&lt;/tt&gt; which may break potential code from people using &lt;tt&gt;Closure#call&lt;/tt&gt; in Java and catching &lt;tt&gt;InvokerInvocationException&lt;/tt&gt; by themselves.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
